e crucial `.env.local` variables set up, along with installing the necessary Supabase packages for SSR compatibility in Next.js 15. The focus is on the `Supabase SSR package` for handling cookies. Also, the folder structure is being re-evaluated for a cleaner organization.\n\n\n**Finalizing the Database Setup**\n\nI\u0027ve decided to prioritize the Supabase SDK for the database connection in my MVP to meet the tight deadline. It will be sufficient for authentication, basic CRUD operations, and even vector matching. I\u0027m focusing on ensuring technical terminology like \"Scaffolding\" and \"Boilerplate\" is accurate in the Catalan text, to polish the presentation. I\u0027ve re-assessed the Prisma situation; while `pgvector` is now supported, the Supabase SDK offers a lighter approach for this portfolio MVP, keeping bundle size and complexity low.\n\n\n",
