      "text": "Entès. Tens tota la raó. 🫡\n\nCom a CTO, accepto la estirada d\u0027orelles. **La disciplina amb l\u0027idioma i el codi net és innegociable.** A partir d\u0027ara:\n1.  **Codi:** Strings en `translations.ts`, res hardcoded.\n2.  **Comentaris:** Strictly English.\n3.  **UI:** Millorem l\u0027UX dels tags (Combobox) i el Filtratge.\n\nAnem a atacar els teus punts QoL (Quality of Life) un per un.\n\n---\n\n### 🧠 Anàlisi Tècnic: IA i Tags (La teva pregunta)\n\n\u003e *\"La IA és capaç de detectar totes les notes amb el tag \u0027Idees\u0027?\"*\n\n**Resposta curta:** Amb el sistema actual (RAG Vectorial), **NO**.\n**Per què?** El RAG busca **similitud semàntica**, no exactitud. Si tens 50 notes amb el tag \"Idees\", el RAG només en recuperarà les 5 (o `match_count`) que més s\u0027assemblin al text de la teva pregunta. La IA no sap que n\u0027hi ha 45 més.\n\n**La Solució (Arquitectura \"Tools\"):**\nPer fer això, hem d\u0027ensenyar a la IA a utilitzar **Eines (Function Calling)**.\n1.  Definim una eina anomenada `get_notes_by_tag(tagName)`.\n2.  Quan l\u0027usuari diu \"Llista les notes amb tag Idees\", la IA (Gemini) detecta que no ha de xerrar, sinó **executar codi**.\n3.  El sistema fa una `SELECT * FROM notes WHERE tags @\u003e \u0027{Idees}\u0027` (cerca exacta SQL).\n4.  La IA rep la llista completa (les 50 notes) i et respon.\n\n**Decisió:** Implementarem això al final d\u0027aquesta fase. Primer, arreglem la UI dels Tags i el Filtratge manual.\n\n---\n\n### 🛠️ Pas 1: Preparar Internacionalització (`src/lib/translations.ts`)\n\nAfegim les claus necessàries per als nous components.\n\n```typescript\nexport const translations \u003d {\n  en: {\n    // ... existing ...\n    common: {\n      tags: \"Tags\",\n      add_tag: \"Add tag...\",\n      search_placeholder: \"Search notes...\",\n      filter_by_tag: \"Filter by tag\",\n      clear_filters: \"Clear filters\",\n      no_results: \"No notes found matching your criteria.\",\n      confirm_delete: \"Are you sure?\",\n      delete_warning: \"This action cannot be undone.\",\n      cancel: \"Cancel\",\n      delete: \"Delete\",\n      edit: \"Edit\",\n      actions: \"Actions\"\n    }\n  },\n  es: {\n    // ... existing ...\n    common: {\n      tags: \"Etiquetas\",\n      add_tag: \"Añadir etiqueta...\",\n      search_placeholder: \"Buscar notas...\",\n      filter_by_tag: \"Filtrar por etiqueta\",\n      clear_filters: \"Limpiar filtros\",\n      no_results: \"No se encontraron notas con estos criterios.\",\n      confirm_delete: \"¿Estás seguro?\",\n      delete_warning: \"Esta acción no se puede deshacer.\",\n      cancel: \"Cancelar\",\n      delete: \"Eliminar\",\n      edit: \"Editar\",\n      actions: \"Acciones\"\n    }\n  },\n  ca: {\n    // ... existing ...\n    common: {\n      tags: \"Etiquetes\",\n      add_tag: \"Afegir etiqueta...\",\n      search_placeholder: \"Cercar notes...\",\n      filter_by_tag: \"Filtrar per etiqueta\",\n      clear_filters: \"Netejar filtres\",\n      no_results: \"No s\u0027han trobat notes amb aquests criteris.\",\n      confirm_delete: \"Estàs segur?\",\n      delete_warning: \"Aquesta acció no es pot desfer.\",\n      cancel: \"Cancel·lar\",\n      delete: \"Eliminar\",\n      edit: \"Editar\",\n      actions: \"Accions\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🏷️ Pas 2: Millorar el Selector de Tags (`TagSelector`)\n\nUtilitzarem un **Combobox** (de Shadcn/UI) que permet cercar tags existents o crear-ne de nous. És molt més net que un input de text pla.\n\nNecessitem el component `Command` i `Popover`. Si no els tens:\n`npx shadcn@latest add command popover`\n\nCrea `src/components/ui/tag-selector.tsx`:\n\n```typescript\n\u0027use client\u0027\n\nimport * as React from \"react\"\nimport { Check, ChevronsUpDown, Plus } from \"lucide-react\"\nimport { cn } from \"@/lib/utils\"\nimport { Button } from \"@/components/ui/button\"\nimport {\n  Command,\n  CommandEmpty,\n  CommandGroup,\n  CommandInput,\n  CommandItem,\n  CommandList,\n  CommandSeparator,\n} from \"@/components/ui/command\"\nimport {\n  Popover,\n  PopoverContent,\n  PopoverTrigger,\n} from \"@/components/ui/popover\"\nimport { Badge } from \"@/components/ui/badge\"\nimport { useLanguage } from \"@/components/language-provider\"\n\ninterface TagSelectorProps {\n  selectedTags: string[]\n  setSelectedTags: (tags: string[]) \u003d\u003e void\n  availableTags: string[] // List of all unique tags in the system\n}\n\nexport function TagSelector({ selectedTags, setSelectedTags, availableTags }: TagSelectorProps) {\n  const [open, setOpen] \u003d React.useState(false)\n  const [inputValue, setInputValue] \u003d React.useState(\"\")\n  const { t } \u003d useLanguage()\n\n  const handleSelect \u003d (currentValue: string) \u003d\u003e {\n    // Toggle logic\n    if (selectedTags.includes(currentValue)) {\n      setSelectedTags(selectedTags.filter((tag) \u003d\u003e tag !\u003d\u003d currentValue))\n    } else {\n      setSelectedTags([...selectedTags, currentValue])\n    }\n  }\n\n  const handleCreate \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\n    if (inputValue \u0026\u0026 !selectedTags.includes(inputValue)) {\n      setSelectedTags([...selectedTags, inputValue])\n      setInputValue(\"\")\n    }\n  }\n\n  return (\n    \u003cdiv className\u003d\"flex flex-col gap-2\"\u003e\n      \u003cPopover open\u003d{open} onOpenChange\u003d{setOpen}\u003e\n        \u003cPopoverTrigger asChild\u003e\n          \u003cButton\n            variant\u003d\"outline\"\n            role\u003d\"combobox\"\n            aria-expanded\u003d{open}\n            className\u003d\"w-full justify-between text-muted-foreground bg-transparent border-input/50\"\n          \u003e\n            {selectedTags.length \u003e 0\n              ? `${selectedTags.length} selected`\n              : t.common.add_tag}\n            \u003cChevronsUpDown className\u003d\"ml-2 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 opacity-50\" /\u003e\n          \u003c/Button\u003e\n        \u003c/PopoverTrigger\u003e\n        \u003cPopoverContent className\u003d\"w-[200px] p-0\" align\u003d\"start\"\u003e\n          \u003cCommand\u003e\n            \u003cCommandInput \n                placeholder\u003d{t.common.search_placeholder} \n                onValueChange\u003d{setInputValue}\n            /\u003e\n            \u003cCommandList\u003e\n              \u003cCommandEmpty className\u003d\"p-1\"\u003e\n                 {/* Create new tag option if it doesn\u0027t exist */}\n                 \u003cButton \n                    variant\u003d\"ghost\" \n                    className\u003d\"w-full justify-start text-xs h-8\" \n                    onClick\u003d{handleCreate}\n                 \u003e\n                    \u003cPlus className\u003d\"mr-2 h-3 w-3\" /\u003e Create \"{inputValue}\"\n                 \u003c/Button\u003e\n              \u003c/CommandEmpty\u003e\n              \n              \u003cCommandGroup heading\u003d{t.common.tags}\u003e\n                {availableTags.map((tag) \u003d\u003e (\n                  \u003cCommandItem\n                    key\u003d{tag}\n                    value\u003d{tag}\n                    onSelect\u003d{() \u003d\u003e handleSelect(tag)}\n                  \u003e\n                    \u003cCheck\n                      className\u003d{cn(\n                        \"mr-2 h-4 w-4\",\n                        selectedTags.includes(tag) ? \"opacity-100\" : \"opacity-0\"\n                      )}\n                    /\u003e\n                    {tag}\n                  \u003c/CommandItem\u003e\n                ))}\n              \u003c/CommandGroup\u003e\n            \u003c/CommandList\u003e\n          \u003c/Command\u003e\n        \u003c/PopoverContent\u003e\n      \u003c/Popover\u003e\n\n      {/* Selected Tags Display */}\n      {selectedTags.length \u003e 0 \u0026\u0026 (\n        \u003cdiv className\u003d\"flex flex-wrap gap-1 mt-1\"\u003e\n          {selectedTags.map((tag) \u003d\u003e (\n            \u003cBadge key\u003d{tag} variant\u003d\"secondary\" className\u003d\"text-xs\"\u003e\n              {tag}\n              \u003cspan \n                className\u003d\"ml-1 cursor-pointer opacity-50 hover:opacity-100\"\n                onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e handleSelect(tag)}\n              \u003e\n                ×\n              \u003c/span\u003e\n            \u003c/Badge\u003e\n          ))}\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n      )}\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  )\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🔍 Pas 3: Barra de Filtratge Avançada (`FilterBar`)\n\nCrearem un component dedicat per filtrar el grid. Aquest component substituirà l\u0027input simple que teníem abans.\n\nCrea `src/components/notes/filter-bar.tsx`:\n\n```typescript\n\u0027use client\u0027\n\nimport { Search, X } from \u0027lucide-react\u0027\nimport { Input } from \u0027@/components/ui/input\u0027\nimport { Button } from \u0027@/components/ui/button\u0027\nimport {\n  Select,\n  SelectContent,\n  SelectItem,\n  SelectTrigger,\n  SelectValue,\n} from \"@/components/ui/select\"\nimport { useLanguage } from \u0027@/components/language-provider\u0027\n\ninterface FilterBarProps {\n  searchTerm: string\n  setSearchTerm: (value: string) \u003d\u003e void\n  selectedTag: string | null // For now we filter by 1 tag at a time in the grid for simplicity\n  setSelectedTag: (tag: string | null) \u003d\u003e void\n  availableTags: string[]\n}\n\nexport function FilterBar({ \n    searchTerm, \n    setSearchTerm, \n    selectedTag, \n    setSelectedTag, \n    availableTags \n}: FilterBarProps) {\n  const { t } \u003d useLanguage()\n\n  const hasActiveFilters \u003d searchTerm || selectedTag\n\n  const clearFilters \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\n    setSearchTerm(\u0027\u0027)\n    setSelectedTag(null)\n  }\n\n  return (\n    \u003cdiv className\u003d\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 mb-6 items-center\"\u003e\n      {/* Search Input */}\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\"relative flex-1 w-full\"\u003e\n        \u003cSearch className\u003d\"absolute left-3 top-1/2 h-4 w-4 -translate-y-1/2 text-muted-foreground\" /\u003e\n        \u003cInput \n          placeholder\u003d{t.common.search_placeholder} \n          className\u003d\"pl-9 bg-background/50 backdrop-blur-sm border-muted-foreground/20\"\n          value\u003d{searchTerm}\n          onChange\u003d{(e) \u003d\u003e setSearchTerm(e.target.value)}\n        /\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      {/* Tag Filter Dropdown */}\n      \u003cSelect \n        value\u003d{selectedTag || \"all\"} \n        onValueChange\u003d{(val) \u003d\u003e setSelectedTag(val \u003d\u003d\u003d \"all\" ? null : val)}\n      \u003e\n        \u003cSelectTrigger className\u003d\"w-full sm:w-[180px] bg-background/50\"\u003e\n          \u003cSelectValue placeholder\u003d{t.common.filter_by_tag} /\u003e\n        \u003c/SelectTrigger\u003e\n        \u003cSelectContent\u003e\n          \u003cSelectItem value\u003d\"all\"\u003eAll Tags\u003c/SelectItem\u003e\n          {availableTags.map(tag \u003d\u003e (\n            \u003cSelectItem key\u003d{tag} value\u003d{tag}\u003e#{tag}\u003c/SelectItem\u003e\n          ))}\n        \u003c/SelectContent\u003e\n      \u003c/Select\u003e\n\n      {/* Clear Button */}\n      {hasActiveFilters \u0026\u0026 (\n        \u003cButton \n            variant\u003d\"ghost\" \n            size\u003d\"sm\" \n            onClick\u003d{clearFilters}\n            className\u003d\"text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground\"\n        \u003e\n            \u003cX className\u003d\"h-4 w-4 mr-2\" /\u003e\n            {t.common.clear_filters}\n        \u003c/Button\u003e\n      )}\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  )\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🧩 Pas 4: Integració al `NoteGrid` i `CreateNoteForm`\n\nAra hem d\u0027actualitzar el `NoteGrid` perquè calculi els tags disponibles (basant-se en les notes que té) i utilitzi la nova `FilterBar`.\n\n**A. Actualitza `src/components/notes/note-grid.tsx`:**\n\n```typescript\n\u0027use client\u0027\n\nimport { useState, useMemo } from \u0027react\u0027\nimport { Card, CardContent, CardFooter } from \u0027@/components/ui/card\u0027\nimport { Badge } from \u0027@/components/ui/badge\u0027\nimport { Trash2, Pencil } from \u0027lucide-react\u0027\nimport { deleteNote } from \u0027@/actions/notes\u0027\nimport { Button } from \u0027@/components/ui/button\u0027\nimport { useLanguage } from \u0027@/components/language-provider\u0027\nimport ReactMarkdown from \u0027react-markdown\u0027\nimport remarkGfm from \u0027remark-gfm\u0027\nimport { toast } from \"sonner\"\n// ... AlertDialog imports ...\nimport { EditNoteDialog } from \u0027./edit-note-dialog\u0027\nimport { FilterBar } from \u0027./filter-bar\u0027 // ✅ Import New Component\n\ninterface NoteGridProps {\n  notes: Array\u003c{ id: number, content: string, created_at: string, tags: string[] | null }\u003e\n}\n\nexport function NoteGrid({ notes }: NoteGridProps) {\n  const { t } \u003d useLanguage()\n  \n  const [searchTerm, setSearchTerm] \u003d useState(\u0027\u0027)\n  const [selectedTag, setSelectedTag] \u003d useState\u003cstring | null\u003e(null)\n  const [editingNote, setEditingNote] \u003d useState\u003c{id: number, content: string, tags: string[]} | null\u003e(null)\n\n  // 🧠 DERIVE AVAILABLE TAGS (Client-side calculation)\n  // This extracts all unique tags from the current notes list\n  const availableTags \u003d useMemo(() \u003d\u003e {\n    const allTags \u003d notes.flatMap(note \u003d\u003e note.tags || [])\n    return Array.from(new Set(allTags)).sort()\n  }, [notes])\n\n  // 🔎 FILTER LOGIC\n  const filteredNotes \u003d notes.filter(note \u003d\u003e {\n    const matchesSearch \u003d note.content.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase())\n    const matchesTag \u003d selectedTag ? (note.tags \u0026\u0026 note.tags.includes(selectedTag)) : true\n    return matchesSearch \u0026\u0026 matchesTag\n  })\n\n  const handleDelete \u003d async (id: number) \u003d\u003e {\n    try {\n      await deleteNote(id)\n      toast.success(\"Deleted\") // Keeping generic, use t.commo